('7273', '1', 'Using vegetable peeler, shave carrots and cucumber lengthwise into ribbons.'),
('7273', '2', 'Cut ribbons into 3-inch-long sections, then cut sections into matchstick-size strips.'),
('7273', '3', 'Place in large bowl.'),
('7273', '4', 'Add shallots, jalapeos, lime juice, sugar, and fish sauce; let marinate 30 minutes at room temperature.'),
('7273', '5', 'Add trout pieces and tomatoes to vegetable mixture and toss to blend.'),
('7273', '6', 'Transfer trout-vegetable mixture to large strainer and drain off liquid. Return trout-vegetable mixture to same bowl; add mint and basil and toss to blend. Arrange lettuce leaves on large platter. Divide trout-vegetable salad among lettuce leaves.'),
('7273', '7', 'Drizzle sweet chili sauce over each salad and sprinkle with peanuts.'),
('7274', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large cast-iron skillet.'),
('7274', '2', 'Add the potatoes and cook over moderate heat, tossing, until tender and golden brown, 5 to 6 minutes.'),
('7274', '3', 'Add the scallions and onion and cook until softened.'),
('7274', '4', 'Add the corn and trout and cook, stirring, until heated through. Season the hash with salt and pepper.'),
('7274', '5', 'In a shallow pan of simmering water, poach the eggs until the whites are set and the yolks are still runny, about 3 minutes.'),
('7274', '6', 'Remove the eggs with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. Mound the hash on plates, top with the eggs and serve at once.'),
('7276', '1', 'Remove the skin, head and tail from the trout. Gently pull the fillets from the bones, leaving even the very fine bones attached.'),
('7276', '2', 'In a mixing bowl, gently shred the fillets with two forks; remove any fine bones now. Set aside.'),
('7276', '3', 'Cook the celery and onion in butter over medium-low heat until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('7276', '4', 'Add, with pepper, to the fish. Cool.'),
('7276', '5', 'Beat the cream until it holds soft peaks. Gently fold into the trout.Refrigerate for at least 3 to 4 hours, or up to 2 days, before using.'),
('7276', '6', 'var article'),
