('7277', '1', 'Place apple halves cut-side up in a baking dish large enough to hold them in a single layer. Sprinkle with sugar and top with bread-crumb mixture.'),
('7277', '2', 'Pour 1/4 cup cider around apples. Cover and bake for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes more or until apples are tender and crumbs are crispy.'),
('7277', '3', 'Remove from the oven.'),
('7279', '1', 'Spread cornbread level in a 10- by 15-inch baking pan.'),
('7279', '2', 'Bake in a 350 oven until dry and lightly toasted, about 20 minutes.'),
('7279', '3', 'Place in a large bowl.'),
('7279', '4', 'Add pumpkin seeds, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper; mix.'),
('7279', '5', 'Meanwhile, tear kale leaves away from tough center stems; discard stems.'),
('7279', '6', 'Cut or tear leaves into 2-inch pieces. In a 5- to 6-quart pan over high heat, bring 2 quarts water to a boil.'),
('7279', '7', 'Add kale and cook until tender to bite, 2 to 3 minutes; drain well. When cool enough to handle, squeeze water from leaves.'),
('7279', '8', 'In a 10- to 12-inch frying pan over medium-high heat, cook bacon, turning often, until browned and crisp; transfer to paper towels to drain.'),
('7279', '9', 'Drain and discard all but 1 teaspoon fat in pan. When bacon is cool enough to handle, crumble and add to cornbread mixture in bowl.'),
('7279', '10', 'Place trout, skin side up, in pan (in batches if necessary) and cook until browned on the bottom, 2 to 3 minutes. Turn with a wide spatula, reduce heat to medium, and cook until fish is barely opaque but still moist-looking in center of thickest part (cut to test), 2 to 4 minutes longer.'),
('7279', '11', 'Transfer trout to a plate and cover with foil to keep warm.'),
('7279', '12', 'Add olive oil and onion to pan and stir often until onion is limp, about 5 minutes. Stir in kale, vinegar, and lemon juice.'),
('7279', '13', 'Add kale mixture to cornbread mixture and mix well.'),
('7279', '14', 'Spoon cornbread salad equally onto four plates and top each serving with a trout fillet.'),
('7280', '1', 'Place smoked trout in mixing bowl, and break into small pieces.'),
('7280', '2', 'Add chives and next 3 ingredients, and combine well. Season with salt and pepper. Chill, covered, until ready to serve.'),
('7281', '1', 'On a work surface, using a thin sharp knife, cut the trout fillets crosswise with the knife held almost flat against the fish to make very thin slices; leave the intact skin behind. Arrange the slices in a large glass baking dish, slightly overlapping them if necessary.'),
('7281', '2', 'In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup of lemon juice with the sugar, juniper berries, whole peppercorns and 2 teaspoons of salt.'),
('7281', '3', 'Pour the marinade over the trout. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours.'),
('7281', '4', 'Using a sharp knife, peel the oranges, limes and grapefruits, removing all of the bitter white pith. Working over a bowl to catch the juice, cut between the membranes to release the sections.'),
('7281', '5', 'Transfer the sections to a large plate and squeeze the membranes over the bowl to release the juice. Discard the membranes.'),
('7281', '6', 'In a small bowl, whisk the olive oil with the remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons of lemon juice, the mustard and reserved citrus juice. Season with salt and the crushed pepper. Toss the mesclun with some of the dressing and mound on plates.'),
('7281', '7', 'Remove the sliced trout from the marinade, scraping off the seasoning, and arrange on the salads.'),
('7281', '8', 'Garnish with the citrus sections, celery and fennel fronds.'),
('7281', '9', 'Drizzle with the remaining citrus dressing and serve right away.'),
('7282', '1', 'Remove and discard skin from fish; finely chop fish.'),
('7282', '2', 'Place fish, sour cream, and mayonnaise in a medium bowl, and mash with a fork. Stir in chopped onion, carrot, and green bell pepper.'),
('7283', '1', 'In a large bowl, stir together the flour, lemon pepper, salt, thyme, cayenne and half of the lemon zest.'),
('7283', '2', 'Combine the lemon juice and remaining lemon zest in a shallow dish and soak fish fillets for about 1 minute.'),
('7283', '3', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Dip the trout fillets in the flour mixture so that both sides are coated. Shake off the excess and place fillets in the hot oil. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until golden brown and fish can be flaked with a fork. Discard the leftover lemon juice.'),
('7283', '4', 'Remove from the skillet and drain on paper towels briefly before serving.'),
('7283', '5', 'Garnish each serving with a wedge of lemon.'),
('7285', '1', 'Mix neufchtel, dill, and lemon zest in a small bowl until blended.'),
('7285', '2', 'Spread 2 tbsp. cheese mixture on each tortilla. Arrange trout down the center, then top with spinach.'),
('7285', '3', 'Heat a medium nonstick frying pan over medium heat.'),
('7285', '4', 'Whisk eggs in a small bowl to blend.'),
('7285', '5', 'Pour eggs into pan and scramble until set, about 2 1/2 minutes.'),
('7285', '6', 'Spoon eggs over spinach on tortillas, then roll up burritos, tucking in ends.'),
('7286', '1', 'In a bowl, combine the cream cheese, shallot, chopped chives, capers and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7286', '2', 'Spread the English muffins with the caper cream cheese. Top with the smoked trout, garnish with the chive pieces and serve.'),
('7287', '1', 'In a wide flat dish, combine the bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, oregano, red pepper flakes, zest of 1 lemon and salt, to taste.'),
('7287', '2', 'In a small bowl, mix together the mustard and the juice of 1 lemon.'),
('7287', '3', 'Brush both sides of the trout with mustard mixture. Coat the fish on both sides with the seasoned bread crumbs and press firmly to adhere the crumbs to the fish.'),
('7287', '4', 'Preheat the oven to 250 degrees F.'),
('7287', '5', 'Coat a large skillet with about 1/4 to 1/2-inch of olive oil and bring to a medium-high heat.'),
('7287', '6', 'Add the fish to the pan, skin side down, and cook the fish 2/3''s of the way, about 6 to 7 minutes. Carefully turn the fish over and cook the other side until the fish is brown and crispy, about 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('7287', '7', 'Remove the fish from the pan and drain on paper towels. You will probably need to work in batches to do 4 fish. After the first batch is done and dried on paper towels reserve it on a rack in a warm oven.'),
('7287', '8', 'When all the fish has been fried, remove the oil and any brown bits from the pan.'),
('7287', '9', 'Add the butter and remaining lemon juice and swirl to combine as the butter melts. Season with salt, to taste, and reduce by about half.'),
('7287', '10', 'Transfer the fish to a serving platter, drizzle with the butter lemon sauce and serve.'),
('7287', '11', 'What a fishtale!'),
('7288', '1', 'Preheat broiler to high.'),
('7288', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('7288', '3', 'Add bacon to pan; saut 4 minutes.'),
('7288', '4', 'Add onion, bell pepper, carrot, thyme, and garlic; saut 4 minutes. Stir in mushrooms; saut 4 minutes.'),
('7288', '5', 'Place in a medium bowl; cool slightly. Stir in crabmeat, parsley, and juice.'),
('7288', '6', 'Open trout flat as you would a book. Sprinkle trout evenly with salt and black pepper. Spoon about 1/4 cup mushroom mixture onto one side of each fish, and fold other side over to cover. Arrange fish on a foil-lined broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Broil 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7288', '7', 'Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.'),
('7289', '1', 'In a large saucepan, cover the potatoes with cold water and bring to a boil. Cook over moderate heat until the outsides are tender but the centers are still hard, about 15 minutes.'),
('7289', '2', 'Drain and cool under running water. Peel the potatoes and coarsely grate them. Season with salt and pepper and toss to combine.'),
('7289', '3', 'Season the trout with salt and pepper. On a cast-iron griddle or skillet, melt 1/2 tablespoon of the butter in 1/2 tablespoon of the oil. Spoon a scant 1/2 cup of shredded potatoes onto the griddle and flatten it into a 5-inch round. Set a piece of trout in the center, cover with a spinach leaf and top with a scant 1/2 cup of potatoes, flattening them. Cook the potato cake over moderately low heat until crispy and golden on the bottom, 5 to 7 minutes. Carefully turn the cake and cook until the potatoes are crisp and golden and the trout is cooked through, about 5 minutes longer; add more butter and oil if necessary.'),
('7289', '4', 'Transfer to paper towels to drain, then serve hot. Repeat with the remaining grated potatoes, trout and spinach, serving the potato-trout cakes hot.'),
('7293', '1', 'Skin the trout and break the fish into large flakes.'),
('7293', '2', 'Transfer the trout to a bowl and add the remaining lemon-caper mayonnaise, chopped olives and red onion; season with salt and pepper. Stir the spread until the fish is broken up but still slightly chunky.'),
('7293', '3', 'Serve with endives, radishes, cucumbers and cauliflower florets.'),
('7294', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.'),
('7294', '2', 'Add watercress and remaining ingredients; toss gently to coat.'),
('7295', '1', 'Place potatoes in a medium saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes or until tender.'),
('7295', '2', 'Drain; cool.'),
('7295', '3', 'Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, red wine vinegar, salt, and freshly ground black pepper in a large bowl, stirring well with a whisk.'),
('7295', '4', 'Add potatoes, Smoked Trout, and remaining ingredients; toss gently to coat.'),
('7296', '1', 'Heat oven to 400 degrees. Arrange fillets in the center of parchment rectangles. Season with salt and pepper and top with tomatoes.'),
('7296', '2', 'Drizzle with oil.'),
('7296', '3', 'Fold parchment closed and transfer to a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('7296', '4', 'Bake until fish is cooked through, 12 to 14 minutes. Top with basil before serving.'),
('7297', '1', 'Heat oven to 400 degrees. Arrange fillets in the center of parchment rectangles. Season with salt and pepper and top with tomatoes.'),
('7297', '2', 'Drizzle with oil.'),
('7297', '3', 'Fold parchment closed and transfer to a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('7297', '4', 'Bake until fish is cooked through, 12 to 14 minutes. Top with basil before serving.'),
('7300', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('7300', '2', 'Remove the skin from the trout. On a rimmed baking sheet, rub the skin with olive oil, then bake for about 10 minutes, until crisp. Flake the trout into 1-inch pieces.'),
('7300', '3', 'In a bowl, whisk the 1/4 cup of oil with the lemon juice; season with salt and pepper.'),
('7300', '4', 'Using a sharp knife, peel the grapefruits, removing all of the bitter white pith. Working over a bowl, cut in between the membranes to release the sections into the bowl.'),
('7300', '5', 'Cut the sections into 1-inch pieces.'),
('7300', '6', 'In a medium bowl, gently toss the avocados with 2 tablespoons of the dressing. In a large bowl, toss the arugula, endives and red onion with 2 tablespoons of the dressing.'),
('7300', '7', 'Add the grapefruit pieces, sliced radishes and smoked trout and the remaining dressing and toss gently.'),
('7300', '8', 'Add the avocados.'),
('7300', '9', 'Spread the salad out on plates. Break the trout skin into shards, scatter over the salads and serve.'),
('7303', '1', 'Remove and discard skin from fish; finely chop fish.'),
('7303', '2', 'Place fish, sour cream, and mayonnaise in a medium bowl, and mash with a fork. Stir in chopped onion, carrot, and green bell pepper.'),
('7304', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 30'),
('7304', '2', 'Cut both types of peppers lengthwise and remove the seeds and veins. Lightly coat a heavy skillet with olive oil. Saut the peppers until they give off their juices and wilt. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('7304', '3', 'Place the trout on a baking sheet and heat in the oven for 10 minutes.'),
('7304', '4', 'Serve with the peppers, fresh lemon wedges, and freshly grated horseradish.'),
('7304', '5', 'var article'),
('7304', '6', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('7304', '7', 'article'),
('7304', '8', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('7305', '1', 'Toast rye bread.  Mince garlic very finely, almost to a paste and mix with butter.  Set aside for the moment.'),
('7305', '2', 'Heat olive oil in saute pan to hot, but not smoking.'),
('7305', '3', 'Add in shallots and peppers and a pinch of sea salt.'),
('7305', '4', 'Saute 2-3 mins over medium heat, until shallots start to get translucent.'),
('7305', '5', 'Add green beans and saute another 5-8 minutes, until everything is tender, but still has a crunch.'),
('7305', '6', 'Add corn kernals and saute 2-3 minutes.  Take pan off of heat, tear basil into large pieces and stir to combine.'),
('7305', '7', 'Heat will wilt basil, but not over cook.'),
('7305', '8', 'Add lemon juice, maple syrup, mustard and 3 tablespoons olive oil and a pinch of sea salt in blender.  Blend until combined.'),
('7305', '9', 'Pour over corn and pepper mixture.  Toss to coat all the veggies.'),
('7305', '10', 'Split corn and pepper mixture between two large soup bowls (use 4 smaller bowls or plates is serving as appetizer).  Break smoked trout into large pieces and divide between bowls, placing it on top of corn mixture.'),
('7305', '11', 'Spread garlic butter on toasted rye bread while it is still warn and serve along side the salad.'),
('7305', '12', 'Garnish with piece of the purple basil for dramatic flair.'),
('7306', '1', 'Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat (fat will rise to the top, and milk solids will sink to the bottom). Skim off white froth that appears on top. Strain off the clear, yellow butter, discarding milk solids. Set aside.'),
('7306', '2', 'Drain and pat grated potato and celery root dry, pressing between paper towels.'),
('7306', '3', 'Combine grated vegetables, corn, and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in flour and egg. Shape vegetable mixture into 24 (2-inch) minicakes.'),
('7306', '4', 'Heat about 2 tablespoons clarified butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook 8 cakes, 7 to 8 minutes on each side or until golden. Repeat procedure with remaining butter and cakes.'),
('7306', '5', 'Place a 1/2-ounce piece of smoked trout on each cake. Top with Horseradish Crme Frache and Golden Beet Relish.'),
('7306', '6', 'Serve warm.'),
('7308', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('7308', '2', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),
('7308', '3', 'Add cranberries; let stand 5 minutes.'),
('7308', '4', 'Spread about 1 teaspoon goat cheese on each bread slice. Arrange bread slices in a single layer on a baking sheet. Broil bread slices 1 minute.'),
('7308', '5', 'Place 1 1/2 cups salad greens on each of 4 plates. Top each serving with 1 3/4 ounces trout and 1 1/2 teaspoons pistachios.'),
('7308', '6', 'Drizzle about 4 teaspoons dressing over each serving.'),
('7308', '7', 'Place 2 cheese toasts on each plate.'),
('7310', '1', 'In a colander, toss the cucumber with  teaspoon of salt and let stand until wilted, about 25 minutes. Pat dry.'),
('7310', '2', 'Meanwhile, soak the guajillo and chipotle chiles in the boiling water until softened, 20 minutes. Discard the stems and seeds and coarsely chop the chiles.'),
('7310', '3', 'Light a grill. Grill the tomatillos over high heat until they are charred all over, about 5 minutes. Discard the charred skins and coarsely chop the tomatillos.'),
('7310', '4', 'In a small skillet, heat the 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil.'),
('7310', '5', 'Add two-thirds of the minced garlic and the onion and cook them over moderate heat until softened, about 7 minutes.'),
('7310', '6', 'Transfer to a blender and add the chopped chiles and tomatillos and the cilantro and mint. Puree the sauce and season with salt and pepper.'),
('7310', '7', 'In a medium bowl, toss the wilted cucumbers with the sour cream, jalapeo, parsley and the remaining minced garlic. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7310', '8', 'Brush the trout fillets with vegetable oil and season with salt and pepper. Oil the grate and grill the fish over high heat, skin side down, until the skin is crisp, about 3 minutes. Turn the fish and grill until it is just cooked through, about 2 minutes longer.'),
('7310', '9', 'Transfer the fish to plates and serve with the chile-tomatillo sauce and cucumber salad alongside.'),
('7313', '1', 'Whisk eggs in large bowl to blend.'),
('7313', '2', 'Add trout, cream cheese, green onions, and chopped dill. Season lightly with salt and generously with pepper; stir to mix.'),
('7313', '3', 'Melt butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('7313', '4', 'Add egg mixture and stir slowly until eggs just hold together and are cooked through but still moist, about 4 minutes. Divide egg mixture among 4 plates.'),
('7313', '5', 'Garnish with dill sprigs, if desired, and serve.'),
('7314', '1', 'In a blender, puree the shallot, vinegars and mustard. Gradually blend in the oils. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7314', '2', 'Arrange the endives, apple, walnuts, trout and watercress on plates.'),
('7314', '3', 'Drizzle with the dressing and serve.'),
('7316', '1', 'Preheat oven to 37'),
('7316', '2', 'Combine squash and thyme in a medium bowl. Crush 1 garlic clove; add to squash mixture.'),
('7316', '3', 'Drizzle with 1 tablespoon oil; sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Toss to coat. Arrange squash mixture in a single layer on a baking sheet; bake at 375 for 40 minutes or until squash is tender; stirring occasionally.'),
('7316', '4', 'Prepare grill.'),
('7316', '5', 'Place 1 garlic clove in a mini food processor; process until finely chopped.'),
('7316', '6', 'Add 2 tablespoons oil, celery leaves, parsley, juice, and 1/8 teaspoon salt; process until finely chopped.'),
('7316', '7', 'Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon salt and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper evenly over trout fillets.'),
('7316', '8', 'Brush fillets with 1 teaspoon oil.'),
('7316', '9', 'Place fillets, skin side down, on a grill rack; grill 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Keep warm.'),
('7316', '10', 'Slice remaining clove of garlic.'),
('7316', '11', 'Heat a large skillet over high heat; add remaining 2 teaspoons oil.'),
('7316', '12', 'Add sliced garlic, onion, and remaining 1/8 teaspoon salt; cook 2 minutes or until onions begin to brown.'),
('7316', '13', 'Add squash mixture; cook 2 minutes or until hot. Stir in pecans; cook 1 minute. Divide squash mixture evenly among 4 plates; top each with a trout fillet. Spoon 2 tablespoons pesto over each trout fillet.'),
('7319', '1', 'Place each trout onto a square of aluminum foil. Open them up so that the flesh is facing upwards. On one side of each fish, season with salt and pepper, half of the garlic, half of the chopped rosemary and half of the parsley. Top each fish with thin slices of butter, 3 rosemary sprigs and a few slices of lemon. Squeeze one of the remaining lemon slices over each fish. Enclose the seasoning inside each fish and wrap securely with the sheet of aluminum foil. Wrap each fish in an additional piece of aluminum foil.'),
('7319', '2', 'Place fish in the coals of a campfire or on a grill over a flame and cook for about 7 minutes on each side. If you can easily stick a fork into the fish, it is done. Cooking time will vary depending on the size of your fish and the fire. Allow to cool for a few minutes before opening to serve.'),
('7320', '1', 'In a medium bowl combine the yogurt, cucumber, dill, lemon zest, olive oil and salt and pepper.'),
('7320', '2', 'Mix well and set aside.'),
('7320', '3', 'Turn oven broiler on. Coat a broiler pan with non-stick cooking spray.'),
('7320', '4', 'Sprinkle fillets with lemon pepper and place on broiler pan. broil for about 8 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork. To serve spoon yogurt sauce over fish.'),
('7321', '1', 'Mix first 4 ingredients in small bowl. Season with freshly ground black pepper. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover; chill. Bring to room temperature before using.)'),
('7321', '2', 'Separate endive into leaves.'),
('7321', '3', 'Spread small amount of cheese mixture on base end of each leaf. Top with trout piece; garnish with small dill sprig. Arrange filled leaves on platter. (Can be made 6 hours ahead. Cover; chill.)'),
('7322', '1', 'Halve the zucchini crosswise.'),
('7322', '2', 'Cut the zucchini flesh off the seedy center and coarsely grate it in a food processor. Or grate it on a box grater until you reach the seedy center. Discard the center. In a food processor or on a box grater, coarsely grate the potato and onion.'),
('7322', '3', 'Transfer the grated zucchini, potato and onion to a colander and squeeze dry.'),
('7322', '4', 'Let stand for 2 minutes, then squeeze again.'),
('7322', '5', 'Transfer the vegetable mixture to a large bowl.'),
('7322', '6', 'Add the matzo meal, egg, lemon juice, salt and pepper and stir to combine.'),
('7322', '7', 'In a medium skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil until shimmering. Drop packed teaspoons of the zucchini mixture into the skillet and flatten them with the back of a spoon. Cook the latkes over moderately high heat until the edges are golden, about 1 1/2 minutes; flip and cook until golden on the bottom, about 1 minute.'),
('7322', '8', 'Drain on paper towels. Repeat with the remaining zucchini mixture, adding more oil to the skillet as needed.'),
('7322', '9', 'Arrange the latkes on a platter and top each one with a dollop of sour cream and a little red pepper jelly, smoked trout and golden trout roe; sprinkle with the scallion greens.'),
('7322', '10', 'Serve warm.'),
('7324', '1', 'In a large salad bowl, break the smoked trout into small pieces, discarding any bones.'),
('7324', '2', 'Tear the frisee and watercress into small pieces and add that the bowl.'),
('7324', '3', 'Shave the fennel and shallots into fine slices and add them to the bowl.'),
('7324', '4', 'Add the apple, fresh dill and several grinds of black pepper.'),
('7324', '5', 'Prepare the dressing by combining all of the dressing ingredients into a jar. Cover and shake vigorously.'),
('7324', '6', 'Pour the dressing over the salad and toss to distribute.'),
('7328', '1', 'Preheat a grill for medium-high heat.'),
('7328', '2', 'On a flat surface, lay out two sheets of aluminum foil about 18 inches long so that they overlap to make one long wide sheet. Rinse the trout and pat dry. Lay the fish in the center of the foil about 2 inches apart. Sprinkle with white wine, melted butter and lemon juice. Season with parsley, salt and pepper. Fold the foil up loosely around the fish and crimp the seams to seal.'),
('7328', '3', 'Place the packet on the grill and cook for 15 to 20 minutes, or until fish is cooked through.'),
('7329', '1', 'In a food processor, combine the fromage blanc, cream cheese, garlic, salt and cayenne and process until smooth.'),
('7329', '2', 'Add the smoked trout and half the orange zest, and pulse a few times just to combine.'),
('7329', '3', 'Transfer to a bowl and gently stir in the snipped chives. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.Scoop the mousse into small souffl dishes or other serving bowls.'),
('7329', '4', 'Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving. Scatter the remaining orange zest and the chive lengths over the top of the mousse and serve with the water biscuits. Makes about 2 cups.Note: For a more pungent spread, double the amount of smoked trout.'),
('7330', '1', 'In a bowl, soak the shiitakes in the tamari-spiked boiling water until softened, about 30 minutes.'),
('7330', '2', 'Drain the mushrooms, reserving 2 tablespoons of the liquid. In a food processor, pulse the mushrooms and the reserved mushroom liquid with the parsley, garlic and shallot until finely chopped. With the machine on, slowly add 1 tablespoon of the oil.'),
('7330', '3', 'Transfer the pesto to a small bowl and season with salt and pepper.'),
('7330', '4', 'Place the trout on a work surface. Using tweezers, remove the fine pin bones that run along the center of each fillet. Coat a large nonstick baking sheet with cooking spray. Arrange the trout, skin side down, on the sheet.'),
('7330', '5', 'Heat the remaining 1 teaspoon of oil in a skillet.'),
('7330', '6', 'Add the leeks and cook over moderately high heat until just wilted, about 3 minutes.'),
('7330', '7', 'Add the wine, season with salt and pepper and cook until the liquid has evaporated, 1 to 3 minutes.'),
('7330', '8', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('7330', '9', 'Sprinkle the trout with the lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.'),
('7330', '10', 'Spread one-quarter of the pesto in a thin layer on each trout. Spoon the leeks on top and bake for about 10 minutes, or just until the trout is cooked through.'),
('7331', '1', 'If using salt-cured capers, put in a small bowl, cover with water, and let soak 10 minutes to remove salt; rinse and pat completely dry. (For brine-packed capers, rinse well and pat dry.)'),
('7331', '2', 'In a 4- to 6-quart pan over high heat, bring 2 to 3 quarts water to a boil.'),
('7331', '3', 'Add potatoes and cook, uncovered, until tender when pierced, about 15 minutes.'),
('7331', '4', 'Drain.'),
('7331', '5', 'Meanwhile, pull off and discard skin from trout. Break the fish into bite-size pieces.'),
('7331', '6', 'Set a 1- to 1 1/2-quart pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add olive oil; when it begins to ripple, add capers (use a potholder and stand back--the oil may splatter). Cook, stirring once, until berries have opened and are light brown and crisp, about 1 minute.'),
('7331', '7', 'Pour into a fine wire strainer over a 1-cup glass measure; reserve oil.'),
('7331', '8', 'Pour capers onto paper towels to drain.'),
('7331', '9', 'In a large serving bowl, whisk oil from capers with lemon juice and pepper. Stir in potatoes.'),
('7331', '10', 'Add trout, apple, and dill and mix gently. Sprinkle fried capers over the top.'),
('7331', '11', 'Serve with sour cream, if desired.'),
('7333', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('7333', '2', 'Cook asparagus in a large saucepan of boiling water 2 minutes.'),
('7333', '3', 'Drain and plunge asparagus into ice water; drain and pat dry.'),
('7333', '4', 'Combine milk and next 4 ingredients (through egg whites) in a medium bowl, stirring with a whisk. Stir in asparagus, 2 tablespoons cheese, dill, and trout.'),
('7333', '5', 'Heat a 10-inch ovenproof skillet over medium heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('7333', '6', 'Add oil and onions to pan; cook 1 minute, stirring occasionally.'),
('7333', '7', 'Pour egg mixture into pan; stir once. Cook without stirring for 2 minutes or until edges begin to set.'),
('7333', '8', 'Place pan in oven.'),
('7333', '9', 'Bake at 450 for 8 minutes or until eggs are just set.'),
('7333', '10', 'Remove from oven; sprinkle evenly with remaining 2 tablespoons cheese.'),
('7333', '11', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('7333', '12', 'Broil frittata 2 minutes or until lightly browned.'),
('7333', '13', 'Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes.'),
('7333', '14', 'Cut into 8 wedges.'),
('7336', '1', 'Soak wood chips in water 30 minutes, and drain well.'),
('7336', '2', 'Combine lemon juice, horseradish, and fillets in a large zip-top plastic bag. Seal and marinate in refrigerator 20 minutes, turning bag occasionally.'),
('7336', '3', 'Prepare grill for indirect grilling, heating one side to low and leaving one side with no heat. Maintain temperature at 200 to 22'),
('7336', '4', 'Place wood chips on hot coals.'),
('7336', '5', 'Place a disposable aluminum foil pan on unheated side of grill.'),
('7336', '6', 'Pour 2 cups water in pan. Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place on grill.'),
('7336', '7', 'Remove fillets from bag; discard marinade. Sprinkle fillets with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('7336', '8', 'Place fillets on grill rack over foil pan on unheated side. Close lid; cook 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7336', '9', 'Combine remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper, vinegar, oil, and chili powder, stirring with a whisk.'),
